  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (synthetic adversarial: inadequate metrics)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence is reported via R-squared and Pearson correlation coefficients computed on the CFD training dataset used to calibrate the power-law hemolysis model coefficients — metrics that characterise goodness-of-fit to historical calibration data rather than predictive accuracy of the relative hemolysis index (RH) under unseen CPB operating conditions.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
